HEADWORD: Cloot
<hw>Cloot</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. G. dial.
<ets>kleuzen</ets> to split.]</ety> <fld>(Scot. & Dial. Eng.)</fld>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>One of the divisions of a cleft hoof, as in the ox;
also, the whole hoof.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>The Devil; Clootie; -- usually in the
<pluf>pl.</pluf></def> <rj><au>Burns.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Clootie</ent>⟦br⟧
